<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="310" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,619,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1852" box="[282,484,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandarinia">
<emphasis box="[282,484,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Vespa mandarinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[845,998,619,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis box="[845,910,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Vespa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
that have been recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[1300,1384,619,645]" name="Canada" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Canada</collectingCountry>
by a combination of the following characters: 1) length of gena at least 1.7 
<emphasis box="[922,941,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">×</emphasis>
as long as eye at midheight as seen in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[220,308,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-22@6.[151,1435,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Vespa mandarinia. A–C. Specimen collected at Nanaimo, British Columbia, Canada. D. Specimen collected in Kyushu, Japan. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Anterior view of head. D. Lateral view of head. el = eye length, gl = gena length, T6 = tergum 6. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6671195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6671195/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
), 2) metasomal terga 3–6 usually with a wide, orange posterior band, terga 3–5 sometimes completely black, but tergum 6 always predominantly orange (
<figureCitation box="[722,810,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-22@6.[151,1435,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Vespa mandarinia. A–C. Specimen collected at Nanaimo, British Columbia, Canada. D. Specimen collected in Kyushu, Japan. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Anterior view of head. D. Lateral view of head. el = eye length, gl = gena length, T6 = tergum 6. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6671195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6671195/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
